About this item

  • (1). [ Easy Installation with WiFi System ] __ This WiFi system includes an 8-channel NVR and 4pcs 3MP IP66 weatherproof C302 cameras. Avoid the hassle of long-distance wiring by simply connecting the cameras and NVR to power using the included adapters. Enjoy 2K HD footage with 100ft night vision. Notice: Both the cameras and NVR require a power connection for continuous 24/7 surveillance.
  • (2). [ Smart AI Human Detection & Instant Notifications ] __ The ZOSI C302 WiFi Camera NVR system features advanced AI human detection to minimize false alarms from moving animals or falling leaves. When motion is detected, recording starts automatically, and a notification is sent to your mobile device. You can also customize the alarm plan and interval.
  • (3). [ Sound & Light Alerts, Two-Way Audio ] __ Designed for proactive security, the ZOSI C302 camera includes two motion-activated white LED warning lights and a siren (up to 85dB) that can be triggered manually from your phone or automatically by human motion events. The built-in speaker and microphone enable two-way audio communication.
  • (4). [ Local or Remote Access, Playback Anytime & Anywhere ] __ Control and view your security system locally by connecting it to a monitor without the internet, or remotely via the free ZOSI Client software on a tablet, PC, or the ZOSI Smart app on mobile devices (ensure the NVR is connected to your router via Ethernet). Easily playback key footage or memorable moments by searching specific days, hours, or minutes.
  • (5). [ 1TB Hard Drive Built-In with Various Recording Modes ] __ The ZOSI NVR offers four recording modes to meet your needs: continuous recording, scheduled recording, motion-detected recording, and recycle recording. Customize each camera’s recording mode and download footage for USB backup.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      3.0 out of 5 stars Mounting is difficult and hard to get to pair me.fpor remote viewing
      Reviewed in the United States on March 2, 2025
      Size: 8CH-4Cam-1TBVerified Purchase
      Overall, the Zosiamera system is decent, but there are a few things I wish I had considered before purchasing. One major drawback is the adjustability of the cameras. Once mounted, they are not easily repositioned, and adjusting the viewing angle requires loosening a screw, which is difficult to do. This makes fine-tuning the placement more frustrating than it should be.

      On the positive side, the setup is straightforward, and the cameras come well-packaged. They pair automatically, which is a big plus. However, I encountered some challenges when setting up remote access to review footage from my phone, which took more effort than expected.

      If you’re looking for a simple plug-and-play system, this might work for you, but if adjustability and seamless remote access are priorities, you may want to explore other options.
